  RELEVANCE: Draper's focus on democratic dimensions of occupancy connects to contractualist concerns about justification: if occupancy rights include governance claims, this intensifies questions about how such exclusionary control can be justified to outsiders. Her work suggests occupancy theory may have more expansive implications than typically recognized, potentially deepening rather than resolving the tension between incumbent and newcomer claims.

